-# WattWise – Campus Energy Intelligence Dashboard
-Local Setup & Usage Instructions
-
-This project is a modern full-stack energy monitoring platform with a cyberpunk-themed interface, built using Node.js + Express backend and vanilla JavaScript frontend.
-
-Important – Two Parts to Run
-1. Frontend (HTML/CSS/JS) – the pages you see in the browser
-2. Backend (server.js) – handles authentication, data processing, and AI features
-
-Both must be running at the same time.
-
-Prerequisites
-• GitHub Codespaces (recommended) or local VS Code
-• Node.js installed (version 18 or higher) – download from: https://nodejs.org
-• npm (comes with Node.js)
-• VS Code extension: Live Server (by Ritwick Dey) – highly recommended
-
-Step 1: Start the Backend (server.js)
-The backend must run first – it listens on port 3000.
-
-1. Open terminal in Codespaces (bottom panel or press Ctrl + ` )
-2. Go to the backend folder:
-
-   cd backend
-
-3. Install dependencies (only needed once):
-
-   npm install
-
-   This installs: express, bcryptjs, cors, jsonwebtoken, dotenv, etc.
-
-4. Start the server:
-
-   node server.js
-
-   You should see:
-   Server running on port 3000
-   Backend ready → http://localhost:3000
-
-   → Keep this terminal open – do not close it.
-
-Step 2: Start the Frontend (pages in browser)
-
-1. In VS Code Explorer sidebar → navigate to the project root.
-2. Go inside the `public/` folder (or `welcome-page/` folder) where your login/register pages are located.
-3. Right-click on `index.html` → select **Open with Live Server**
-
-   → Browser opens at something like:
-
-   http://127.0.0.1:5500/public/index.html
-
-   or (in Codespaces):
-
-   https://your-codespace-name-5500.app.github.dev/public/index.html
-
-4. You should now see the styled login page with the cyberpunk theme (neon accents, dark background, futuristic fonts).
-
-Step 3: How to Test
-
-There are no default users – you must register first.
-
-Register a new user:
-1. On the login page → click "Sign up" / Register link
-2. Fill in:
-   • Username: choose anything (example: adminuser, teststudent, energyadmin)
-   • Password: at least 6 characters
-   • Confirm Password: same as above
-3. Click REGISTER
-4. You should see a success message and be redirected back to the login page.
-
-Log in:
-1. Use the exact credentials you just registered.
-2. Click SIGN IN / LOGIN
-3. Expected result:
-   • Successful login message
-   • Redirect to the main dashboard (dashboard.html)
-
-After login, explore:
-- Block-wise energy monitoring (GH, BH, AB1, AB2, ADM)
-- AI Energy Assistant
-- Forecasting dashboard
-- Anomaly alerts
-- CSV data upload (Admin only)
-- Light/Dark mode toggle
-
-Happy testing!
-
-Any questions → check terminal output or browser console (press F12).
\ No newline at end of file
